    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i've seen a lot of people calling these 'existential risks' just a distraction or even hype to help big companies get ahead of smaller competitors through regulation. do you think those arguments carry much weight, or is the risk to humanity actually a more scientifically grounded concern?",
